00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:14.730
for less structured
sets of data.

00:13:14.730 --> 00:13:18.390
So images that we
might have from as sort

00:13:18.390 --> 00:13:22.420
of like project collateral, sort
of the visual representation

00:13:22.420 --> 00:13:24.980
of models as opposed to
their data representation,

00:13:24.980 --> 00:13:27.580
we can begin to scan these
and use machine vision

00:13:27.580 --> 00:13:31.630
to classify them in
historically interesting ways.

00:13:31.630 --> 00:13:35.210
So I'll mention an example,
not directly archival

00:13:35.210 --> 00:13:37.080
but with archival implications,

00:13:37.080 --> 00:13:38.780
here we see a machine
vision algorithm --

00:13:38.780 --> 00:13:42.270
or, sorry, this is an example
of a façade which the way

00:13:42.270 --> 00:13:44.130
that the human would see
it on the left and the way

00:13:44.130 --> 00:13:46.440
that the machine would
see it on the right,

00:13:46.440 --> 00:13:48.860
and from this network
