00:37:36.210 --> 00:37:39.210
to do an exhibition of
a major project of his,

00:37:39.210 --> 00:37:40.950
the Tel Aviv Museum of Art.

00:37:40.950 --> 00:37:43.850
I was asked to help reconstruct
part of the design process

00:37:43.850 --> 00:37:45.800
and I did some of
the preliminary work

00:37:45.800 --> 00:37:48.660
and it was installed at Harvard.

00:37:48.660 --> 00:37:51.210
Reconstructing the
design process would seem

00:37:51.210 --> 00:37:53.340
to be relatively
straightforward.

00:37:53.340 --> 00:37:57.130
The project was designed by a
small number of people and most

00:37:57.130 --> 00:37:58.430
of them were still around.

00:37:58.430 --> 00:38:01.270
It was an entirely
digital project.

00:38:01.270 --> 00:38:04.420
A range of models and drawings
from the very beginning

00:38:04.420 --> 00:38:07.580
of the project coexisted in
the firm's project archive,

00:38:07.580 --> 00:38:11.120
so this is sort of a
picture of what you would see

00:38:11.120 --> 00:38:14.860
at the opened -- yes, that
folder on their server.

00:38:14.860 --> 00:38:18.300
And it existed in more or
less the same structure

00:38:18.300 --> 00:38:23.460
as when it was being worked on,
so the organization was ad hoc,

00:38:23.460 --> 00:38:25.230
let's say, but it
