00:52:27.450 --> 00:52:28.750
and see them together.

00:52:28.750 --> 00:52:32.580
It has things like the
drawings in the 3D models,

00:52:32.580 --> 00:52:35.820
but also a figure
background kind of views,

00:52:35.820 --> 00:52:39.340
different analyses,
images of course.

00:52:39.340 --> 00:52:42.780
And then maybe most
interestingly

00:52:42.780 --> 00:52:46.240
as a segway 3D models that talk

00:52:46.240 --> 00:52:48.150
about the different
circulation paths,

00:52:48.150 --> 00:52:51.400
so from what I understand, you
guys may know better than me,

00:52:51.400 --> 00:52:56.800
but courthouses have a very
sort of mission critical idea

00:52:56.800 --> 00:53:00.010
about which different
constituencies,

00:53:00.010 --> 00:53:02.660
I mean basically the
judiciary goes one way,

00:53:02.660 --> 00:53:05.730
the public goes another way,
the indicted go a different way

00:53:05.730 --> 00:53:07.300
and you have to keep
them separate.

00:53:07.300 --> 00:53:10.390
And in a three space
configuration that's actually

00:53:10.390 --> 00:53:12.810
fairly challenging, it's
challenging to understand, too.

00:53:12.810 --> 00:53:17.910
So this system is I think
complementary to some

00:53:17.910 --> 00:53:20.670
of the design guidelines
that would be associated

00:53:20.670 --> 00:53:25.100
with courthouses and sort of
present an archive of some

00:53:25.100 --> 00:53:28.190
of the critical things
that are in that guideline

00:53:28.190 --> 00:53:30.730
and that the GSA and
the court systems care

00:53:30.730 --> 00:53:32.030
about for those buildings.

00:53:32.030 --> 00:53:35.320
So it's seen as kind of
a database and archive

00:53:35.320 --> 00:53:36.820
of again different features

00:53:36.820 --> 00:53:40.270
of those different projects
that you can compare.

00:53:40.270 --> 00:53:45.300
So those are the two
