00:53:45.300 --> 00:53:47.480
of this kind of digital
archiving.

00:53:47.480 --> 00:53:53.110
And then from there I
want to quickly go to some

00:53:53.110 --> 00:53:55.850
of the more rarified stuff
around design language.

00:53:55.850 --> 00:53:58.450
So I thought this was an
original thought when I came

00:53:58.450 --> 00:54:01.690
up with this slide,
but on the left --

00:54:01.690 --> 00:54:04.600
okay, so on the left
obviously the Rosetta Stone,

00:54:04.600 --> 00:54:07.490
in the middle Andrew talked
about Christopher Alexander

00:54:07.490 --> 00:54:10.620
and pattern language, on
