01:40:34.570 --> 01:40:37.180
of OpenBIM, okay?

01:40:37.180 --> 01:40:38.630
What do we mean by OpenBIM?

01:40:38.630 --> 01:40:40.830
When we talk about BIM we talk

01:40:40.830 --> 01:40:42.320
about building information
modeling.

01:40:42.320 --> 01:40:45.930
When we talk about OpenBIM what
we're trying to do is remove

01:40:45.930 --> 01:40:48.440
that proprietary
layer, we're saying

01:40:48.440 --> 01:40:51.540
that the data is more important
than the tools, themselves.

01:40:51.540 --> 01:40:55.100
And so as architects, as
engineers, as designers,

01:40:55.100 --> 01:40:59.740
as owners, as operators
we should have access

01:40:59.740 --> 01:41:03.260
to that information in a
way that's completely free

01:41:03.260 --> 01:41:07.320
of any particular tool so that
we can move it from tool to tool

01:41:07.320 --> 01:41:12.190
and operate with that
information as we need.

01:41:12.190 --> 01:41:15.750
So as an organization
buildingSMART is international

01:41:15.750 --> 01:41:19.580
and it's supported by the
