02:17:44.290 --> 02:17:47.290
&gt;&gt; I have a question for Roger.

02:17:47.290 --> 02:17:48.590
&gt;&gt; Roger Grant: Okay.

02:17:48.590 --> 02:17:49.890
&gt;&gt; Hi, Roger.

02:17:49.890 --> 02:17:51.190
&gt;&gt; Roger Grant: Hi, Christine.

02:17:51.190 --> 02:17:54.040
&gt;&gt; I'm Christine Falon from
Christie Falon Associates.

02:17:55.220 --> 02:17:58.010
Product data, now in
manufacturing if you go

02:17:58.010 --> 02:18:03.760
to aerospace stuff is sort of
custom made for a plane, right?

02:18:03.760 --> 02:18:09.040
But we use a lot of stuff, what
we call off-the-shelf products

02:18:09.040 --> 02:18:11.130
in our buildings, right?

02:18:11.130 --> 02:18:16.950
And what I'm running into in
implementations I'm doing is

02:18:16.950 --> 02:18:22.950
this kind of great babble
of product data, you know,

02:18:22.950 --> 02:18:27.420
what are the properties, what
are the appropriate properties

02:18:27.420 --> 02:18:30.800
for a tiller and where
do I get the properties.

02:18:30.800 --> 02:18:35.310
And at this point it's an
incredible stupid manual thing.

02:18:35.310 --> 02:18:40.190
Is there any movement in
getting manufacturers to agree

02:18:40.190 --> 02:18:44.400
on standard property
sets for their products

02:18:44.400 --> 02:18:47.700
and delivering them
in a standard format?

02:18:47.700 --> 02:18:50.360
&gt;&gt; Roger Grant: Well,
manufacturers have worked

02:18:50.360 --> 02:18:52.710
to make their information
available online,

02:18:52.710 --> 02:18:55.440
but they haven't structured
it in a common way.

02:18:55.440 --> 02:18:59.170
I think that there is movement
in Europe on this subject

02:18:59.170 --> 02:19:02.590
because there are EU regulations
that require manufacturers

02:19:02.590 --> 02:19:06.450
to report information about
their products in a certain way

02:19:06.450 --> 02:19:08.290
and about aspects
of their products.

02:19:08.290 --> 02:19:12.850
So that's driving in
Europe a SEN standard,

02:19:12.850 --> 02:19:14.240
a common European standard

02:19:14.240 --> 02:19:17.090
for how product data
templates should be made.

02:19:17.090 --> 02:19:19.010
We're going to adopt
that in buildingSMART

02:19:19.010 --> 02:19:20.890
and have it be a
buildingSMART standard.

02:19:20.890 --> 02:19:24.850
We're looking at it originating
from IFC because I mean

02:19:24.850 --> 02:19:28.300
that an object has
properties and so all

02:19:28.300 --> 02:19:29.600
that stuff can be structured.

02:19:29.600 --> 02:19:32.290
So I think it's going to
get here, it's starting more

02:19:32.290 --> 02:19:34.530
so in Europe, and I think
we'll see that because many

02:19:34.530 --> 02:19:36.460
of the manufacturers
are worldwide.

02:19:36.460 --> 02:19:37.840
&gt;&gt; Jeff Ouellette: If
you haven't figured

02:19:37.840 --> 02:19:42.180
out the common thread or trend
here it's not always starting

02:19:42.180 --> 02:19:44.780
in the US.

02:19:44.780 --> 02:19:48.650
And the fact of the matter
is if you look, to be honest,

02:19:48.650 --> 02:19:53.510
amongst all the software vendors
at least in our industry most

02:19:53.510 --> 02:19:58.280
of us make the majority
of our money outside

02:19:58.280 --> 02:20:01.340
of the United States,
simple as that.

02:20:01.340 --> 02:20:04.340
The United States is a big
market, but the majority

02:20:04.340 --> 02:20:06.580
of our money is made
outside the United States.

02:20:06.580 --> 02:20:12.300
In 2011 it's a $7 trillion
building industry from design

02:20:12.300 --> 02:20:18.370
through production, only $1.7
trillion of it was generated

02:20:18.370 --> 02:20:23.560
in the US, $3.5 trillion
was China alone, okay?

02:20:23.560 --> 02:20:27.190
So we, again, it's context,
right, we have to look

02:20:27.190 --> 02:20:28.490
at the bigger picture of this.

02:20:28.490 --> 02:20:29.790
So if significant parts

02:20:29.790 --> 02:20:33.570
of our global market are pushing
this forward then we adopt it

02:20:33.570 --> 02:20:34.870
and it moves forward

02:20:34.870 --> 02:20:36.190
and it becomes a
standard everywhere else,

02:20:36.190 --> 02:20:38.590
whether they like it or not.

