02:21:09.290 --> 02:21:10.590
&gt;&gt; Jessica Meyerson: Sure.

02:21:10.590 --> 02:21:12.400
So Tim mentioned this earlier
in the day, so we're kind

02:21:12.400 --> 02:21:14.800
of talking about different
sets of stakeholders

02:21:14.800 --> 02:21:17.090
and we're talking about
different tax associated

02:21:17.090 --> 02:21:18.670
with those different
sets of stakeholders.

02:21:18.670 --> 02:21:23.780
So I think future forward
standards approach makes perfect

02:21:23.780 --> 02:21:25.080
sense, right?

02:21:25.080 --> 02:21:26.850
It's still a complex
digital object,

02:21:26.850 --> 02:21:29.520
so ultimately you are going to
have to deal with those layers

02:21:29.520 --> 02:21:32.300
of mediation that
